  "prompt": "I tell my crush that I just broke with my girlfriend then I accidentally told her I like her, What should I do now?",
  "response": "First, take a deep breath\u2014it\u2019s okay! It sounds like you were being honest, and that\u2019s a good thing. Here\u2019s what you can do now:\n\n1. **Acknowledge the situation**: If you feel comfortable, you can address the fact that you mentioned your feelings. For example, say something like, \u201cI realize I kind of blurted that out, but I meant it.\u201d\n\n2. **Give her space**: She might need time to process everything you\u2019ve shared. Respect her feelings and avoid putting pressure on her to respond immediately.\n\n3. **Be honest and clear**: If you genuinely like her, let her know in a calm and thoughtful way. For example, \u201cI didn\u2019t mean to make things awkward, but I do have feelings for you. I just thought you should know.\u201d\n\n4. **Listen to her response**: Pay attention to how she reacts and what she says. She might not feel the same way, or she might need time to figure things out. Be open to whatever her response is.\n\n5. **Take it one step at a time**: If she\u2019s open to exploring things with you, great! Take it slow and build a connection. If she\u2019s not interested, respect her boundaries and focus on moving forward.\n\nRemember, being honest about your feelings is brave, and it\u2019s better to express yourself than to wonder \u201cwhat if.\u201d Whatever happens, you\u2019ve handled it with authenticity, and that\u2019s something to be proud of. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
